<BaseLayout title="Rewards Credit Cards - TrueCred Loan Expert | Earn Points on Every Spend">

<!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <a href="/pages/credit-cards">Credit Cards</a>
        <span class="sep"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></span>
        <span>Rewards Credit Cards</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Rewards Credit Cards</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Turn every swipe into valuable rewards. Earn points on daily spends and redeem them for flights, hotel stays, gift vouchers, merchandise, and statement credits across India's top reward programs.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-gift"></i> Up to 33X Rewards
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-tags"></i> 100+ Partner Brands
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-rotate"></i> Flexible Redemption
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Content -->
  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">

        <div class="content-main">

          <h2>Best Rewards Credit Cards in India</h2>
          <p>Rewards credit cards are designed for people who want to earn value back on their everyday spending. Every transaction you make — groceries, dining, fuel, online shopping, or travel bookings — earns reward points that can be accumulated and redeemed for a wide range of benefits. The best rewards cards offer accelerated earning rates on specific categories, generous welcome bonuses, and milestone rewards that significantly boost your total returns.</p>
          <p>India's top rewards cards from HDFC, SBI, ICICI, and Axis Bank offer earning rates ranging from 2 to 33 reward points per ₹100 spent, with redemption values between ₹0.20 and ₹1.00 per point. Choosing the right card can yield returns of 2-5% on your annual spending — far better than a savings account interest rate.</p>

          <h2>Key Features of Rewards Credit Cards</h2>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Accelerated Earning:</strong> Earn up to 10X-33X reward points on partner merchant spends and select categories</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Welcome Bonus:</strong> Get 500-5,000 bonus reward points on card activation and first transaction</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Milestone Rewards:</strong> Earn additional bonuses on reaching quarterly or annual spending milestones</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Flexible Redemption:</strong> Redeem points for flights, hotels, Amazon vouchers, merchandise, or statement credits</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>No Expiry:</strong> Many top rewards cards offer points that never expire as long as your account is active</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Transfer Partners:</strong> Premium cards allow point transfers to airline and hotel loyalty programs at favourable ratios</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Top 5 Rewards Credit Cards for 2026</h2>
          <p>Compare the highest-earning rewards cards available in India right now.</p>

          <table class="rate-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Card Name</th>
                <th>Annual Fee</th>
                <th>Reward Rate</th>
                <th>Key Benefits</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>HDFC Regalia Gold</strong></td>
                <td>₹2,500</td>
                <td>4 RP per ₹150 (up to 10X)</td>
                <td>SmartBuy 10X, 12 lounge visits, milestone vouchers</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>SBI SimplyCLICK</strong></td>
                <td>₹499</td>
                <td>10X on partners, 5X online</td>
                <td>₹500 Amazon welcome voucher, fuel surcharge waiver</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Axis Privilege</strong></td>
                <td>₹1,500</td>
                <td>10 EDGE points per ₹200</td>
                <td>Buy-1-Get-1 movies, dining discounts, travel rewards</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>ICICI Sapphiro</strong></td>
                <td>₹3,500</td>
                <td>2 RP per ₹100 (up to 20X)</td>
                <td>Golf access, concierge, lounge visits, insurance</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>HDFC Infinia</strong></td>
                <td>₹12,500</td>
                <td>5 RP per ₹150 (up to 33X)</td>
                <td>Unlimited lounge, 1:1 airmile transfer, concierge</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>

          <h2>Eligibility for Rewards Credit Cards</h2>
          <p>Here's what you need to qualify for popular rewards credit cards in India:</p>

          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Age:</strong> 21-60 years (salaried) or 21-65 years (self-employed); add-on cards from 18 years</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Income:</strong> ₹25,000/month minimum for mid-tier rewards cards; ₹50,000+ for premium rewards cards</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Credit Score:</strong> CIBIL score of 720+ recommended; 750+ for premium rewards cards like HDFC Infinia</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Spending Pattern:</strong> Regular monthly spending of ₹15,000+ helps justify a rewards card over a basic card</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Employment:</strong> Salaried employees, self-employed professionals, or business owners with documented income</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Documents:</strong> PAN Card, Aadhaar, latest 3-month salary slips or 2-year ITR, bank statements</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>How to Apply for a Rewards Credit Card</h3>
          <p>Start earning reward points on every spend — apply in 4 simple steps:</p>

          <div class="steps-grid">
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">1</div>
              <h4>Choose Your Card</h4>
              <p>Pick the rewards card that aligns with your top spending categories and lifestyle</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">2</div>
              <h4>Verify Eligibility</h4>
              <p>Check income requirements and credit score thresholds to ensure high approval odds</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">3</div>
              <h4>Submit Documents</h4>
              <p>Upload your KYC and income proof through our secure digital application portal</p>
            </div>
            <div class="step-card">
              <div class="step-num">4</div>
              <h4>Start Earning</h4>
              <p>Get approved within 48 hours and start earning reward points from your very first swipe</p>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="content-sidebar">

          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-file-alt" style="color: var(--primary); margin-right: 8px;"></i> Apply Now</h3>
            <form class="sidebar-form">
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Full Name" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="tel" class="form-input" placeholder="Mobile Number" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <select class="form-input">
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Monthly Income</option>
                  <option value="below-15k">Below ₹15,000</option>
                  <option value="15k-25k">₹15,000 - ₹25,000</option>
                  <option value="25k-50k">₹25,000 - ₹50,000</option>
                  <option value="50k-1l">₹50,000 - ₹1,00,000</option>
                  <option value="above-1l">Above ₹1,00,000</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <select class="form-input">
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Employment Type</option>
                  <option value="salaried">Salaried</option>
                  <option value="self-employed">Self Employed</option>
                  <option value="business">Business Owner</option>
                  <option value="student">Student</option>
                  <option value="freelancer">Freelancer</option>
                </select>
